{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":875,"text":"Design is a slippery\nand elusive phenomenon,"},{"time":3921,"text":"which has meant different\nthings at different times."},{"time":7206,"text":"But all truly inspiring design projects\nhave one thing in common:"},{"time":11498,"text":"they began with a dream."},{"time":13679,"text":"And the bolder the dream,"},{"time":15141,"text":"the greater the design feat\nthat will be required to achieve it."},{"time":18806,"text":"And this is why the greatest\ndesigners are almost always"},{"time":22724,"text":"the biggest dreamers\nand rebels and renegades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26787,"text":"This has been the case throughout history,"},{"time":29594,"text":"all the way back to the year 300 BC,"},{"time":33539,"text":"when a 13-year-old became the king"},{"time":36682,"text":"of a remote, very poor\nand very small Asian country."},{"time":41475,"text":"He dreamt of acquiring land,\nriches and power"},{"time":44984,"text":"through military conquest."},{"time":46675,"text":"And his design skills --"},{"time":48082,"text":"improbable though it sounds --"},{"time":49929,"text":"would be essential\nin enabling him to do so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53605,"text":"At the time,"},{"time":54779,"text":"all weapons were made by hand\nto different specifications."},{"time":58213,"text":"So if an archer ran out\nof arrows during a battle,"},{"time":61543,"text":"they wouldn't necessarily be able\nto fire another archer's arrows"},{"time":65490,"text":"from their bow."},{"time":67362,"text":"This of course meant that they would\nbe less effective in combat"},{"time":70947,"text":"and very vulnerable, too."},{"time":73339,"text":"Ying solved this problem"},{"time":74965,"text":"by insisting that all bows and arrows\nwere designed identically,"},{"time":79080,"text":"so they were interchangeable."},{"time":80835,"text":"And he did the same for daggers,\naxes, spears, shields"},{"time":84861,"text":"and every other form of weaponry."},{"time":88002,"text":"His formidably equipped army\nwon batter after battle,"},{"time":91932,"text":"and within 15 years,"},{"time":93746,"text":"his tiny kingdom had\nsucceeded in conquering"},{"time":96928,"text":"all its larger, richer,\nmore powerful neighbors,"},{"time":99777,"text":"to found the mighty Chinese Empire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103041,"text":"Now, no one, of course,"},{"time":104594,"text":"would have thought of describing\nYing Zheng as a designer at the time --"},{"time":108396,"text":"why would they?"},{"time":109628,"text":"And yet he used design\nunknowingly and instinctively"},{"time":113455,"text":"but with tremendous ingenuity"},{"time":115439,"text":"to achieve his ends."},{"time":117631,"text":"And so did another equally\nimprobable, accidental designer,"},{"time":122195,"text":"who was also not above using\nviolence to get what he wanted."},{"time":126376,"text":"This was Edward Teach, better known\nas the British pirate, Blackbeard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132012,"text":"This was the golden age of piracy,"},{"time":134301,"text":"where pirates like Teach\nwere terrorizing the high seas."},{"time":137998,"text":"Colonial trade was flourishing,"},{"time":139991,"text":"and piracy was highly profitable."},{"time":142276,"text":"And the smarter pirates like him\nrealized that to maximize their spoils,"},{"time":147139,"text":"they needed to attack\ntheir enemies so brutally"},{"time":151790,"text":"that they would surrender on sight."},{"time":153607,"text":"So in other words,"},{"time":154782,"text":"they could take the ships\nwithout wasting ammunition,"},{"time":157352,"text":"or incurring casualties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159417,"text":"So Edward Teach redesigned\nhimself as Blackbeard"},{"time":163106,"text":"by playing the part of a merciless brute."},{"time":165794,"text":"He wore heavy jackets and big hats\nto accentuate his height."},{"time":169843,"text":"He grew the bushy black beard\nthat obscured his face."},{"time":173362,"text":"He slung braces of pistols\non either shoulder."},{"time":176933,"text":"He even attached matches to the brim\nof his hat and set them alight,"},{"time":180855,"text":"so they sizzled menacingly\nwhenever his ship was poised to attack."},{"time":185009,"text":"And like many pirates of that era,"},{"time":187605,"text":"he flew a flag that bore\nthe macabre symbols"},{"time":190518,"text":"of a human skull\nand a pair of crossed bones,"},{"time":194002,"text":"because those motifs had signified death\nin so many cultures for centuries,"},{"time":199717,"text":"that their meaning\nwas instantly recognizable,"},{"time":202603,"text":"even in the lawless, illiterate\nworld of the high seas:"},{"time":206167,"text":"surrender or you'll suffer."},{"time":208667,"text":"So of course, all his sensible\nvictims surrendered on sight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212646,"text":"Put like that,"},{"time":214000,"text":"it's easy to see why Edward Teach\nand his fellow pirates"},{"time":218699,"text":"could be seen as pioneers\nof modern communications design,"},{"time":223198,"text":"and why their deadly symbol --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":225146,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":226232,"text":"there's more --"},{"time":227407,"text":"why their deadly symbol\nof the skull and crossbones"},{"time":230416,"text":"was a precursor of today's logos,"},{"time":232730,"text":"rather like the big red letters\nstanding behind me,"},{"time":236101,"text":"but of course with a different message."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238304,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":239332,"text":"Yet design was also used to nobler ends"},{"time":242366,"text":"by an equally brilliant and equally\nimprobable designer,"},{"time":246604,"text":"the 19th-century British nurse,\nFlorence Nightingale."},{"time":250464,"text":"Her mission was to provide\ndecent healthcare for everyone."},{"time":255367,"text":"Nightingale was born into a rather\ngrand, very wealthy British family,"},{"time":259807,"text":"who were horrified when she volunteered\nto work in military hospitals"},{"time":263872,"text":"during the Crimean War."},{"time":265963,"text":"Once there, she swiftly realized"},{"time":268316,"text":"that more patients were dying\nof infections that they caught there,"},{"time":271953,"text":"in the filthy, fetid wards,"},{"time":273945,"text":"than they were of battle wounds."},{"time":275722,"text":"So she campaigned\nfor cleaner, lighter, airier clinics"},{"time":280032,"text":"to be designed and built."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282389,"text":"Back in Britain,"},{"time":283598,"text":"she mounted another campaign,"},{"time":285112,"text":"this time for civilian hospitals,"},{"time":287194,"text":"and insisted that the same design\nprinciples were applied to them."},{"time":291496,"text":"The Nightingale ward, as it is called,"},{"time":294272,"text":"dominated hospital design\nfor decades to come,"},{"time":297976,"text":"and elements of it are still used today."},{"time":301834,"text":"But by then,"},{"time":303113,"text":"design was seen as a tool\nof the Industrial Age."},{"time":306165,"text":"It was formalized and professionalized,"},{"time":308915,"text":"but it was restricted to specific roles"},{"time":311432,"text":"and generally applied in pursuit\nof commercial goals"},{"time":314534,"text":"rather than being used intuitively,"},{"time":316833,"text":"as Florence Nightingale, Blackbeard\nand Ying Zheng had done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321412,"text":"By the 20th century,"},{"time":322906,"text":"this commercial ethos was so powerful,"},{"time":325943,"text":"that any designers who deviated from it"},{"time":328491,"text":"risked being seen as cranks\nor subversives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332538,"text":"Now among them is one\nof my great design heroes,"},{"time":336378,"text":"the brilliant László Moholy-Nagy."},{"time":338930,"text":"He was the Hungarian artist and designer"},{"time":341721,"text":"whose experiments with the impact\nof technology on daily life"},{"time":346001,"text":"were so powerful"},{"time":347191,"text":"that they still influence\nthe design of the digital images"},{"time":350515,"text":"we see on our phone and computer screens."},{"time":353658,"text":"He radicalized the Bauhaus Design\nSchool in 1920s Germany,"},{"time":358379,"text":"and yet some of his former\ncolleagues shunned him"},{"time":361150,"text":"when he struggled to open a new\nBauhaus in Chicago years later."},{"time":366194,"text":"Moholy's ideas were as bold\nand incisive as ever,"},{"time":370432,"text":"but his approach to design\nwas too experimental,"},{"time":374183,"text":"as was his insistence\non seeing it, as he put it,"},{"time":377691,"text":"as an attitude, not a profession\nto be in tune with the times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382782,"text":"And sadly, the same applied"},{"time":384659,"text":"to another design maverick:\nRichard Buckminster Fuller."},{"time":389167,"text":"He was yet another\nbrilliant design visionary"},{"time":392881,"text":"and design activist,"},{"time":394322,"text":"who was completely committed\nto designing a sustainable society"},{"time":398910,"text":"in such a forward-thinking way"},{"time":400814,"text":"that he started talking about\nthe importance of environmentalism"},{"time":404178,"text":"in design in the 1920s."},{"time":407632,"text":"Now he, despite his efforts,"},{"time":410109,"text":"was routinely mocked as a crank\nby many in the design establishment,"},{"time":414866,"text":"and admittedly,"},{"time":416058,"text":"some of his experiments failed,"},{"time":417875,"text":"like the flying car\nthat never got off the ground."},{"time":420893,"text":"And yet, the geodesic dome,"},{"time":422965,"text":"his design formula to build\nan emergency shelter"},{"time":426313,"text":"from scraps of wood, metal, plastic,"},{"time":429018,"text":"bits of tree, old blankets,\nplastic sheeting --"},{"time":432288,"text":"just about anything\nthat's available at the time --"},{"time":435059,"text":"is one of the greatest feats\nof humanitarian design,"},{"time":438654,"text":"and has provided sorely needed refuge"},{"time":441341,"text":"to many, many people\nin desperate circumstances"},{"time":444588,"text":"ever since."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446446,"text":"Now, it was the courage\nand verve of radical designers"},{"time":450508,"text":"like Bucky and Moholy"},{"time":452384,"text":"that drew me to design."},{"time":454681,"text":"I began my career as a news journalist\nand foreign correspondent."},{"time":458741,"text":"I wrote about politics, economics\nand corporate affairs,"},{"time":462183,"text":"and I could have chosen\nto specialize in any of those fields."},{"time":466033,"text":"But I picked design,"},{"time":467801,"text":"because I believe it's one of the most\npowerful tools at our disposal"},{"time":471533,"text":"to improve our quality of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475755,"text":"Thank you, fellow TED design buffs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478357,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":480045,"text":"And greatly as I admire the achievements\nof professional designers,"},{"time":484477,"text":"which have been extraordinary and immense,"},{"time":487096,"text":"I also believe"},{"time":488581,"text":"that design benefits hugely\nfrom the originality,"},{"time":492098,"text":"the lateral thinking"},{"time":493440,"text":"and the resourcefulness\nof its rebels and renegades."},{"time":497683,"text":"And we're living at a remarkable\nmoment in design,"},{"time":501653,"text":"because this is a time when the two camps\nare coming closer together."},{"time":506481,"text":"Because even very basic advances\nin digital technology"},{"time":510796,"text":"have enabled them to operate\nincreasingly independently,"},{"time":515104,"text":"in or out of a commercial context,"},{"time":517542,"text":"to pursue ever more ambitious\nand eclectic objectives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522615,"text":"So in theory,"},{"time":524285,"text":"basic platforms like crowdfunding,\ncloud computing, social media"},{"time":529596,"text":"are giving greater freedom\nto professional designers"},{"time":533064,"text":"and giving more resources\nfor the improvisational ones,"},{"time":536573,"text":"and hopefully,"},{"time":537754,"text":"a more receptive response to their ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540671,"text":"Now, some of my favorite\nexamples of this are in Africa,"},{"time":544862,"text":"where a new generation of designers"},{"time":547013,"text":"are developing incredible\nInternet of Things technologies"},{"time":550582,"text":"to fulfill Florence Nightingale's dream\nof improving healthcare"},{"time":555210,"text":"in countries where more people\nnow have access to cell phones"},{"time":558782,"text":"than to clean, running water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560991,"text":"And among them is Arthur Zang."},{"time":563642,"text":"He's a young, Cameroonian design engineer"},{"time":566536,"text":"who has a adapted a tablet\ncomputer into the Cardiopad,"},{"time":570705,"text":"a mobile heart-monitoring device."},{"time":573152,"text":"It can be used to monitor the hearts\nof patients in remote, rural areas."},{"time":577517,"text":"The data is then sent\non a cellular network"},{"time":580187,"text":"to well-equipped hospitals\nhundreds of miles away"},{"time":583241,"text":"for analysis."},{"time":584441,"text":"And if any problems are spotted\nby the specialists there,"},{"time":587770,"text":"a suitable course of treatment\nis recommended."},{"time":591018,"text":"And this of course saves many patients"},{"time":593353,"text":"from making long, arduous, expensive\nand often pointless journeys"},{"time":598582,"text":"to those hospitals,"},{"time":599924,"text":"and makes it much, much likelier"},{"time":602227,"text":"that their hearts\nwill actually be checked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605298,"text":"Arthur Zang started working\non the Cardiopad eight years ago,"},{"time":608644,"text":"in his final year at university."},{"time":611391,"text":"But he failed to persuade\nany conventional sources"},{"time":614830,"text":"to give him investment to get\nthe project off the ground."},{"time":618281,"text":"He posted the idea on Facebook,"},{"time":620178,"text":"where a Cameroonian\ngovernment official saw it"},{"time":622858,"text":"and managed to secure\na government grant for him."},{"time":626119,"text":"He's now developing\nnot only the Cardiopad,"},{"time":629179,"text":"but other mobile medical devices\nto treat different conditions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633831,"text":"And he isn't alone,"},{"time":635501,"text":"because there are many other\ninspiring and enterprising designers"},{"time":640448,"text":"who are also pursuing\nextraordinary projects of their own."},{"time":644364,"text":"And I'm going to finish\nby looking at just a few of them."},{"time":647934,"text":"One is Peek Vision."},{"time":650213,"text":"This is a group of doctors\nand designers in Kenya,"},{"time":653312,"text":"who've developed an Internet of Things\ntechnology of their own,"},{"time":656545,"text":"as a portable eye examination kit."},{"time":659639,"text":"Then there's Gabriel Maher,"},{"time":661585,"text":"who is developing a new design language"},{"time":663683,"text":"to enable us to articulate the subtleties\nof our changing gender identities,"},{"time":668827,"text":"without recourse\nto traditional stereotypes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671736,"text":"All of these designers and many more\nare pursuing their dreams,"},{"time":676027,"text":"by the making the most\nof their newfound freedom,"},{"time":678677,"text":"with the discipline\nof professional designers"},{"time":681599,"text":"and the resourcefulness\nof rebels and renegades."},{"time":684525,"text":"And we all stand to benefit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686611,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687798,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}